    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it didnt feel like fatigue though. it was too precise. like, i saw the exact same shape of a building reflected in a puddle, but the building itself didn't exist in that spot. it felt less like a brain thing and more like the world just... skipped a frame. do you think there's any scientific reason why reality would actually have glitches like that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
