      "content": "The idea of reality itself having \"glitches\" is a fascinating concept that leans heavily into the realm of theoretical physics and perception. If the experience felt precisely like a skipped frame, it could be an example of visual persistence or perceptual anomaly where your brain is briefly misinterpreting incoming data. Scientifically, this kind of perfectly repeating or displaced imagery is highly unusual, but it speaks to how complex our visual processing is.",
      "source": "target",
