      "content": "i dont know... the more i think about it, the less it feels like my brain is just failing me. it feels like i'm seeing behind the curtain. like if you were playing a massive open world game and the engine started struggling to render everything perfectly, you'd see these exact kinds of artifacts. do you think the simulation theory could actually explain this? like, if we are in a simulation, these glitches would be a logical consequence of the system running out of resources.",
